article.headline: Rider 89, Delaware 84
article.story: LAWRENCEVILLE, N.J. (AP) -- Edwin Muniz had 27 points -- including his 1,000th career point -- to lead Rider to an 89-84 win over Delaware on Saturday. Terrance Mouton added 18 points and four assists for Rider (3-4), while Lamar Johnson had 16 points. Harding Nana had a game-high 28 points and 19 rebounds for Delaware (2-6), while Zaire Taylor had 13 points and five assists. After trailing 51-50 at halftime, Rider went on a 12-6 run midway through the second half. The run was capped off by Muniz's 3-point play, giving him 1,001 career points. The two teams then continued to trade baskets before Rider took control with an 18-6 run late in the second half, including eight points by Johnson, and never trailed again. Overall, the game featured 12 ties and six lead changes.
